article.headline: Sacramento St. 75, North Dakota 64
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Heath Hoffman scored 19 points and Joe Eberhard added 13 as Sacramento State used a late surge for a 75-64 victory against North Dakota on Sunday night. The Hornets (5-5) led 56-55 before going on a 14-4 run over a 4:14 stretch, with 3-pointers by Eberhard and Dylan Garrity highlighting the spree. Jamal Webb had 21 points and Aaron Anderson 14 for the Fighting Sioux (5-6). Sacramento State, which trailed 35-29 at the break, made 7 of 8 3-point attempts in the second half. Hoffman was 4 of 5 from behind the arc for the game. He had two 3-pointers during a 12-0 run by the Hornets in the first 4:32 of the second half. Troy Huff had 10 points for North Dakota.
